[3] Cholera, diarrhea - Bangladesh (Dhaka District)
Date: Thu 18 Mar 2010
Source: The New Nation [edited]
<http://nation.ittefaq.com/issues/2010/03/18/news0460.htm>


As many as 30 patients reported to have cholera are being admitted
each hour at the Mohakhali Cholera Hospital, most of which are
children and the elderly.

Between 15 and 16 Mar 2010, 942 patients were admitted to the
hospital and another 264 were admitted on 17 Mar 2010 after being
affected by the waterborne infection of cholera, hospital sources
said.

Sources said the number of patients of diarrhea, dysentery, and all
kinds of waterborne diseases is increasing alarmingly. Most of those
are coming from Moghbazar, Khilgaon, Banani, Mugda, Lalbagh, Mirpur,
Tejgaon, Mohakhali, and Madhubagh areas [in Dhaka District].

Relatives of the patients said they are getting infected of different
diseases after drinking polluted water supplied by the Dhaka Water
Supply and Sewerage Authority (WASA).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The areas mentioned in the posting are located around the capital
city of Dhaka. Maps of Bangladesh can be found at
